<h3>Search Building Records</h3>
<p>Residents who wish to view Building Department records can search online or by appointment at the Government Center.</p>
<p><strong>Online</strong></p>
<div tabindex="0" aria-expanded="true" role="button">
<div></div>
</div>
<div aria-hidden="false" visibility="visible">
<ul>
    <li>To get a copy of the Field Card for each address using Assessor Database&nbsp;<a href="http://gis.vgsi.com/stamfordct/" target="_blank" tabindex="0">Click Here</a></li>
    <li>To research Historical Permits, Certificate of Occupancy and Certificate of Completion issued between 1950 and October 2013 using Municipal Search database&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="https://www.stamfordct.gov/?splash=https%3a%2f%2fstamfordapps.org%2fMunicipalSearches%2flogin.aspx&amp;____isexternal=true" target="_blank" tabindex="0">Click Here</a></li>
    <li>To research Information on Permits issued after October 2013 using ViewPoint Cloud&nbsp;<a href="https://stamfordct.portal.opengov.com/search" target="_blank" tabindex="0">Click Here</a></li>
</ul>
<h3>Research Requests</h3>
<p>If you would like to request a document from the Building Department, please fill out a&nbsp;<a href="https://stamfordct.portal.opengov.com/categories/1083/record-types/6551" target="_blank">Building Department Customer Inquiry</a></p>
<ul>
    <li>Please allow sufficient time for a response (minimum five (5) working days)<br>
    or call (203) 977-4164&nbsp;to check if your request has been completed</li>
</ul>
</div>
